Bio-Community version 0.01
==========================

THIS MODULE IS IN EARLY DEVELOPMENT STAGE! VERY LITTLE IS USEABLE RIGHT NOW AND
IT IS PROBABLY BUG-RIDDEN!

Bio::Community is a set of BioPerl modules to represent and manipulate communities
of biological organisms.


INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Build.PL
   ./Build
   ./Build test
   ./Build install


DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  BioPerl version > 1.006902 (as of May 2012, this means an unreleased development version)
  Method::Signatures
  Moose
  Moose::Util::TypeConstraints
  MooseX::NonMoose
  MooseX::StrictConstructor
  Parallel::Iterator
  Test::Number::Delta

These other modules are strongly recommended:
 
  Clone


